Author: l8orre
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: remember there is this dichotomy between utility value and pure speculation value.  basically all crypto projects that build some utility value beyond being pure monetary medium (BTC, LTC) are in the production phase right now, and none have been able to show anything in terms of real world usability at all yet.  so this is the production phase, as opposed to the speculation phase, which is over.  the ones that succeed in delivering on their goals -> MOON, the others -> toilet.  so Bitboost suffering from a lack of speculational hype is really not relevant to their ultimately delivering a working and successful product.  Now having said that: The platform is techincally very solid and already in advanced beta stages of development under a reliable and competent team, so I am very optimistic about it!  only Bitcointalk is not a forum for differentiated discussions, so this is why many projects have reduced the amount of energy they spend on this troll infested bilge...

Author: kronos123
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: I have always supported and defended BBT, I have hoped that the team reacts to provocations and accusations, showing the work done, but I was a fool not to sell in January and abandon this project.  Almost 9 months have passed since the pre-ico, 7 months from the ico and 14 months from bitcointalk presentation, and we have:  beta that almost nobody knows, but above all nobody uses  no contact or quotation on any exchange (dex are not exchange therefore do not say that it is on two exchanges, and Yobit is the worst!), after more than 1 year of presentation to the savers  almost no team update here in bitcointalk and no news or reassurance of the delisting from coinmarketcap  In a market fast, explosive and innovative, like the crypto market, waiting all these months is almost like a suicide .... especially in the sector where Bitboost wants to operate. When you start Amazon or eBay or Alibaba with your own blockchain and your internal token (with relative discounts and promotions compared to fiat), what do you think common users will do? What do you think investors and savers will do? What fate will there be for Bitboost?   I hope with all my heart to make mistakes and regret my choice .... as BBT returns to the market, on a decent exchange, I will sell everything and I will pass on to something else!

Author: S3cco
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Bitcoin Garden: BitBoost’s blockchain marketplace goes live in June! https://bitcoingarden.org/bitboosts-blockchain-marketplace-goes-live-in-june/  BitBoost will launch its decentralised marketplace in June. The project, which is built using Ethereum’s smart contracts, will enable buyers and sellers to connect directly – facilitating free and private online commerce.  The marketplace takes the form of a downloadable piece of software that connects to the Ethereum blockchain via either BitBoost’s node or a local node, if preferred. Payments for goods are made in ETH, and all listings cost a flat fee of just $1, payable in the BBT token. The team has worked hard to replicate the look and feel of traditional e-commerce platforms, with instant search and product images hosted on Imgur for anonymity.  “We think this is going to be a game-changing decentralised e-commerce solution,” says founder and CEO Paul Mahone. “We believe in free trade, and the BitBoost marketplace entirely removes several common barriers and intermediaries in online commerce. Anyone can sign up for an account. You don’t need to submit an email address or any personal details: all that is required is an Ethereum address. The interface is clean and familiar, payments are fast and borderless, and privacy is built in.”....

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Like one of the team members stated,  due to the Swiss regulatory institution, FINMA, which is issuing new rules, it is better to wait for that, to avoid legal implications. While, bbt is launching a carefully crafted sellers program, to onboard as many sellers as possible. Any marketplace requires liquidity on the supply side to succeed, and liquidity means sellers. Building this liquidity is not about shilling the token, rather It is about reaching and talking with potential sellers, something that obviously goes unnoticed in social media and the blog. As soon as Bitboost have these sellers willing to accept cryptocurrencies for exchange of their goods and services and they board on this platform, it will launch a regular digital marketing campaign to attract buyers, the other side of the coin, to gain liquidity in the demand side. With liquidity in both sides, hopefully we will get the network effect, the key for the success of any marketplace. In this case, there will be much more listing, more listing means more tokens purchased, more tokens purchased means a higher price of the token. Do you see the mechanism? Everyone is focused on listings which team is working hard to get it listed on more exchanges, but I would say look at the bigger picture of the puzzle and see how these indices fit in to each other to create a continuous stream of token demand based on an actual marketplace.

Author: gartmah
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: The history of BitBoost team.  The BitBoost team has been working together for years on their blockchain marketplace. We are not talking about a rush-for-the-ICO half-baked idea, but a practical application born of the innovative thinking of some real pioneers, who started coding on the blockchain as far back as spring 2014. They saw a need, and an opportunity. Three years later, The Block is a reality and moving towards beta testing.  The initial BitBoost team first met within the community of the blockchain platform NXT, and they built their first marketplace – NXT FreeMarket, a downloadable, functional shopping app on the NXT blockchain. This project was started by Paul Mahone, our CEO, and Andrew Lekar, who was involved in NXT blockchain from the beginning. In the following video, you can watch Paul introducing this app in Amsterdam in 2016.  However, the limitations of the NXT blockchain for a marketplace quickly became apparent and the user base was limited from the outset. Seeing these issues as roadblocks to future success, the team decided to move to the Ethereum blockchain in the summer of 2016. At this time they were joined by Samuele Maran, who was in charge of initial marketing and business operations. These three are the founders of the BitBoost project.  Shortly after, several more people joined to help to craft The Block. Maksim Sergeev started working on the user interface early this year, as the founders recognized the non-technical challenges of a decentralized marketplace to user adoption, such as the requirement to localize The Block in many different languages and to tailor and adapt it for the needs of widely varying legal jurisdictions. The team also incorporated developers to craft mobile apps, such as Riccardo Scanavacca for iOS, and Gianluigi Davassi. BitBoost believes that mobile e-commerce has a strong future, so the plan is to make The Block mobile friendly from the very beginning, allowing people from both mature and developing markets to use the app on their smart phones.  As a result, we have been developing The Block app, in its current Ethereum form, for more than one year. Specifically, we have expended more than 7 months and 222 days crafting the code. You are welcome to join us for beta testing!  As the application was going through development, the team decided to start building a business around it. BitBoost started researching markets and business models (read more about this in our white paper). The team expanded to include people from digital business and marketing, to form the backbone for a fundamentally sound company. Alessandro Tozzi, from Boston Entrepreneurship Center, and Alvaro Rodriguez, in charge of marketing and communications, were added. Yessin Schiegg, a seasoned financial and blockchain expert, joined as an advisor at the same time. Finally, we became officially registered as a company in Zug, also known as Crypto Valley, in May 2017.  Now, BitBoost is facing a last sprint towards launching at the end of 2017. A token sale to fund The Block will be announced this summer, but unlike the vast majority of these events, BitBoost is not asking for money based solely on an idea. Tokens will be sold to use on an existing platform, as soon as we go live. You will have less time to wait before you can actually use them.  The BitBoost team is confident that 2018 will be a great year. With a running app, and many ideas for more features to implement, you will see The Block expand within the e-commerce and digital platform markets, redefining services through the blockchain and decentralization. Updates will come soon. Stay tuned!  https://www.bitboost.net/blog/bitboost-team-history/

Author: Eldest
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Hi all! 2 fresh news for BitBoost - The Block  One: since we have been unable to find a suitable escrow partner for the tokens we intend to lock until November 2018, we have created a smart contract to lock them. The blog post will have the contract address, and we welcome feedback on it before we use it.   Two: we will be doing a burn of 50,000,000 BBT. This will cut the maximum supply in half. We are just finalizing the logistics of how to do it, but it will happen as soon as we figure that out.

Author: BitcoinOnFire
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: I think you can forget about marketing and promotion. ICO failed proved it's not the strongest area of the current team. At least untill they change sth or get someone for that position. But ICO was not much money, so probably there will be none for marketing. A bit pitty project moved from KMD platform to ETH. Also not true this project is totally fresh. The orig one was Freemarket on NXT platform. And the final Freemarket shares CAP was > then current BBT cap after new ICO. Hard to say it's success. Also not much communication. But was neither in the past. Big questionmark. If the team will not change communication/marketing/pr approach wont get much credibility, and that one is also needed to get to another exchange as a trusted solution worth sth. Maybe even overall strategy review is needed. I think there is a few other solution on the market. First one will take it all - like amazon. Tech is one part,  getting good relation with publicity 2nd. Also a community is needed as it helps verify assumptions and grow the product while resources are limited. Here I do not see community, just group of investors. Growing community and attracting people is a different skill. You need an enthusiast visionary with some charisma. Of course commercial success can be there even without community, but community helps a lot in crypto. And if you are able to build community (sells skills here) then you can also sell the solution to final customers. Similar skills: building enthusiasm based on a vision. Sth that tech guys do not always get or see as important. Let's see what will be there in 12 months.

Author: Hashbunker
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Maybe these issues have been raised earlier (I didn’t read the whole tread):  A project like this has the chicken and egg problem. Sellers won’t sign up unless there is a big market already using the site. Buyers won’t use the site unless there are a lot of sellers. So it’s extremely hard to launch a service like this.  In order for people to use the service it needs to have clear and big benefits. I don’t really see any at all with this service unless you are a trying to sell/buy stolen or illegal goods.  If I understand correctly the listings will not be censored? If so, that’s really unethical and will contribute to creating a brand image of a service used by criminals and perverts. No reputable seller will want to have anything to do with the service and there will be boycott campaigns.  The existing market places today are not really expensive at all and already have the users sellers want. And the users can pay with fiat, which almost all prefer to do.  Just some thoughts.

The purpose is to maintain confidence in the project and to ensure that these tokens cannot be sold. This will be achieved using a smart contract or multi-signature escrow.These remaining tokens will be sold at a significantly higher price than the initial pre-sale tranche of 25 million and the main-sale tokens.

Author: Vorteqs
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: If the Bitboost platform does not store data since they take privacy seriously does this mean they promote anonymity of its users,  would certain person's use this to perpetuate fraudulent acts?

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Bitboost honours the privacy of its users using encryption,   but privacy through encryption does not mean anonymity. Users can exchange their personal information as needed through the app. This will be needed for delivery and invoicing purposes, as in any e-commerce service. But, unlike other e-commerce services, The Block does not store this data. It will be safely encrypted into the Ethereum blockchain.

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: To begin with, The Block will protect buyers and sellers with a system that scores users on reliability and trustworthiness based on feedback after completed transactions. This is similar to the system that eBay and many other e-commerce platforms use; merchants who offer consistently high-quality products, good communication and prompt and reliable delivery will naturally receive better feedback, and their enhanced reputation will lead to future business. This crowd-sourced reputation system will provide a first line of defence against substandard merchants and outright scammers. The Block does not require any personal information for users to access its services. No email addresses are collected as a condition of registration/use. Merchants and customers create their own aliases when they begin using the platform. BitBoost does not send messages to anyone as a matter of policy, and the absence of user information collected means there are few channels by which to do so anyway. Although sellers will need to upload images for their products, these can be hosted on free, private web services such as imgur.com All communication between buyer and seller is encrypted using a session key that is generated when an item is purchased. That is, a new key is generated for each interaction and the old one discarded; keys are not reused. Hope this answers your questions.

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Yes,  There are four steps you need to take in order to convert your FreeMarket assets to BBT.  1. Create an Ethereum wallet that is able to accept BBT To create this Ethereum wallet,  visit https://www.myetherwallet.com/ and use the “Create New Wallet” function on the home page.  2: Send your FreeMarket assets to Bitboost. Open your NXT wallet and click on the Assets box. On the next page, find FreeMarket in your list of assets, and click the “Transfer” button in that row. For the Recipient field, use this address: NXT-5ZNG-7DLM-7ZQJ-CQS8P.(this is BBT recepient address) For the quantity, this should be your entire balance of FM assets. When you transfer your FreeMarket assets, be sure to include the address of your new Ethereum wallet. You can do this by checking the “Add a Message?” option. Enter your wallet address in the Message field. Check the boxes for “Encrypt Message” and “Message is Never Deleted.” Enter your account passphrase and click the “Submit” button.  3. Prepare your wallet to accept BBT You will need three pieces of information in order to prepare your wallet correctly: – Address: 0x1500205f50bf3fd976466d0662905c9ff254fc9c – Token Symbol: BBT – Decimals: 4 After you log in to your wallet, click the “Add Custom Token” button under “Token Balances.”  4. Wait BBT will be released after the main sale ends on November 9, 2017. Once the tokens have been released, you may leave them in Orderbook, send them to your wallet in The Block, or send them to your MyEtherWallet Detailed here: https://www.bitboost.net/blog/swap-freemarket-assets-bitboost-tokens/

Author: poofknuckle
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: The beta test invitations have been sent to everyone who signed up.  A few things to note:  - There are three versions, one for macOS, one for Windows, and one for Linux. The Linux version hasn't been tested on every flavor of Linux, so we'd appreciate feedback on that. (And feedback on everything, of course!)  - You will need test ether in order to buy anything, and test BBT in order to list anything. Your invitation email has instructions on how to get those.  - There is one known issue that we are trying to deal with: the app runs on the Ropsten test network, and computationally expensive operations, like listing an item, have become infuriatingly slow recently, so we are working on a fix, either to the app, or by setting up a private test network. We'll have a fix as soon as possible, hopefully by the end of the week.  Thank you for your help with testing! Please break things

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: If you understand the function of an escrow,  then this shouldn't be a problem. Here is a simple explanation, in traditional e-commerce stores, Buyer sends money to purchase an item, this money is held in escrow, while seller sends product purchased. Funds would only be released to seller until buyer has affirmed that he has received item and is satisfied. If there is discrepancies in item or goods did not arrive, buyer would open a dispute after resolution, funds would be returned back to buyer. Now for Bitboost, same principle applies using it's escrow system, payment for the item is held in an escrow contract and will be only released to the seller if both parties indicate that they are satisfied, or if a given period of time has passed without the buyer having opened a dispute. If a dispute is opened, the designated arbiter will be granted control over the escrowed funds and must determine whether they should be returned to the buyer, transferred to the seller, or to both in some ratio depending on resolution. So with this no seller would run away with your money when you purchase item.  Bitboost went an extra mile to introduce proposed reputation system where every seller and buyer will have a reputation rating derived from their conduct and the quality of their products during and after every transaction. Users with a low or negative reputation score may be filtered out, in order to protect all sellers and buyers from fraud and wasted time. Hope my explanation helps you have a better understanding?

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: If you talk about Bitboost database then you are talking about a centralized network. From what I understand in its core features is that the Block has no centralized authority as it's built on the Ethereum blockchain using smart contracts. Transactions are completed in a trustless manner, with no third party involvement, which means no one has to rely on trust for the system to work. Transactions cannot be censored. Listed items are available at all times, to everyone, with no need for sellers to stay online 24/7, since The Block runs on thousands of computers worldwide. This makes it resistant to the kinds of attacks that force conventional websites offline. Decentralization equals greater privacy, freedom, and stability.

Body: Of what use is the arbiter,  isn't it better to deal directly with seller and avoid the complications that may be involved.

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: The option of arbitration, in the case of a dispute between buyer and seller, will be included in The Block. A seller may optionally name an arbiter in an item listing. Payment for the item is held in an escrow contract and will be only released to the seller if both parties indicate that they are satisfied, or if a given period of time has passed without the buyer having opened a dispute. If a dispute is opened, the designated arbiter will be granted control over the escrowed funds and must determine whether they should be returned to the buyer, transferred to the seller, or to both in some ratio. The arbiter may request a fee for this service. Over time, some arbiters will gain a positive reputation for their impartial service and fairness.

Author: wolfgb888
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Encryption works together with smart contracts. The Block utilizes Ethereum smart contracts to list items for sale, to organize the buy and sell process, to hold escrowed funds, and to allow communication between buyers and sellers. Smart contracts enable a transparent and safe trading process. Messages, mandatory to the purchasing process, are stored on the blockchain. Non-mandatory and private communications can be moved to an off-blockchain platform to reduce costs and improve speed. As all data on the Ethereum blockchain are publicly visible, private communication requires encryption. The Block uses the elliptic curve Curve25519 for private-public keypair generation. On a high- level summary, each Curve25519 user has a 32- byte secret key and a 32-byte public key. Each set of two Curve25519 users has a 32-byte shared secret used to authenticate and encrypt messages between the two users.              Advanced encryption standard (AES) is used for data encryption, and one-time private keys are generated for the buy session. One-time keys allow the buyer and seller to share their communication with a third party, e.g. the arbiter, without revealing their private keys. The Block shares private keys for both encrypted communication and Ethereum wallet generation. The private key is stored in the user data folder in JSON format, encrypted with the user’s password.

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: I have read that although transactions will be on the blockchain, The Block is fully encrypted. Messages between buyer and seller are encrypted, and personal information (such as shipping address) is also encrypted by default. Your information is protected from any kind of leak or attack.BitBoost does not use encryption to promote trade in illegal items or to foster a scam ecosystem, but does reflect lessons learned from the mass violations of privacy that have occurred in recent years. A decentralized, blockchain-based system is less prone to theft of personal information. But it needs strong cryptography to protect that data Moreover, privacy through encryption does not mean anonymity. Users can exchange their personal information as needed through the app. This will be needed for delivery and invoicing purposes, as in any e-commerce service. But, unlike other e-commerce services, The Block does not store this data. It will be safely encrypted into the Ethereum blockchain it is exposed on the public blockchain. This is simply brilliant and intriguing, with this no other project offers what Bitboost is bringing on board the e-commerce sector

Author: tutankhamun333
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: How much money does bitboost gained from this business?

Author: enigmatical
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: Bitboost only make money by charging 1 USD (in BitBoost tokens) per listing. The Block doesn’t charge a fee to purchase items. Even image hosting is free, and The Block takes no percentage from your final sale price. Also, a transaction on The Block consists of four parties: the seller, the buyer, the arbiter, and the escrow contract. The seller may choose the arbiter when he lists the item. Arbiters will set their own fees for their service, either a fixed price or a percentage of the item's selling price. The arbiters also determine whether the fee is only charged in the case of a dispute or if it is due regardless of any use of the arbitration service.

Author: wolfgb888
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: In simple terms, cryptoeconomics is the use of incentives and cryptography to design new kinds of systems, applications, and networks. Cryptoeconomics is specifically about building things, and has most in common with mechanism design – an area of mathematics and economic theory. Cryptoeconomics is not a subfield of economics, but rather an area of applied cryptography that takes economic incentives and economic theory into account. Bitcoin, ethereum, zcash and all other public blockchains are products of cryptoeconomics.

ENCRYPTION IS BUILT IN Although all transactions are on the blockchain, not everything is public. Author: wolfgb888
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: From transaction records to payment system, the global e-commerce sector which is projected to increase to $4.058 tln by 2020 needs the Blockchain to evolve with the growing trend, particularly in the Ethereum market. Statista notes that the number of people buying goods or services online will increase from 1.46 bln in 2015 to above two bln in 2020.               Justas Pikelis says this of the e-commerce decentralized “E-commerce needs the Blockchain technology to keep up with the future. Blockchain is the perfect tool for e-commerce to be more efficient and more trustful. For example, payment processing through Blockchain has a significantly bigger potential for transaction high speeds and low prices, let alone all the possible variety of ways smart contracts can improve both e-commerce and payments. In Monetha's case, the Decentralised Trust and Reputation System is the best proof for that. The powerful benefits that DTRS brings would be impossible without the Blockchain technology.”

Author: BitBoost
Title: [ANN][BBT] BitBoost - The Block - Decentralized Ecommerce on Ethereum Blockchain
Body: eBay, Amazon, and Alibaba are the biggest. They will not be disappearing any time soon. Some people will always prefer them, because they are big and familiar. But for sellers, they are very costly.  We expect that sellers will want to move to an alternative that lowers their costs, and if they then lower their prices, that will attract buyers. Sellers and buyers both need to be aware of The Block, so this is where marketing becomes important. It's not enough to have a better product, people also need to know about it.
